                 <h3 class="mt-4">About Us</h3>
                 <p>The network of 41 specialized research libraries in our country joins hands together to make this Digi-Library for providing resources and 
                     services that are as diverse and deep as the collections. 
                     They truly span the range of scientific and cultural pursuits of 
                     humanity from aerospace, anthropology, and art history to business history and botany, cultural history, design, philately, 
                     zoology, and much, much more. While sharing the values, methods, and efficiencies of a unified network, each library in the system 
                     supports the work of its own community of interest comprising specialized researchers and museum curators, as well as visiting scholars, 
                     educators, students, and others pursuing or advancing knowledge in their fields.
                    </p>
